<br>
[b]Shout Of Reflection.[/b]<br>
This is a shout spell that affects all friendly realm members in a 750 unit radius (not just group members).  It lasts 30 seconds and is on a 10 minute timer.  It reflects both melee and magic damage back at the enemy who hit/cast you.  The amount of damage reflected is based partially on the level of shout and partially on the resist of the party member that is hit.  I'll  use heat damage as an example here.<br>
<br>
Lets say player x has a 25% resist to fire.  When a 200 dmg fire spell hits him, it removes 25% or 50 dmg and he actually gets hit for 150 (-50).  If that same player has recently been in range of the Shout Of Reflection.  x% of that 50 he resisted is targetted back at the caster based on the level of Shout used.  If the lvl 8 shout has been used, only 20% or 10 dmg gets redirected at the caster.  If the lvl 44 shout is used, all 50 dmg gets reflected.<br>
<br>
8     20% Of Resisted Damage Is Reflected<br>
16   40% Of Resisted Damage Is Reflected<br>
24   60% Of Resisted Damage Is Reflected<br>
34   80% Of Resisted Damage Is Reflected<br>
44   100% Of Resisted Damage Is Reflected<br>
<br>
Personally I like the idea of this....it could really help in keep defense when Dot's and AE's are flying.  If you feel that this is too strong to be a shout in our songbook, I wouldn't mind seeing it as a replacement to FotG either.<br>
<br>
Sideshow lvl50 Skald<br>
